The  Czech Republic  defeated France to
win tennisâ€™s Hopman Cup for the second time.  Wimbledon champion Petra Kvitova beat Marion Bartoli 7-5,
6-1 and Tomas Berdych defeated Richard Gasquet 7-6 6-4 to give
the Czech Republic a 2-0 victory in the best-of-three final in
Perth, Australia. The Czechs previously won the annual mixed-
team competition in 1994.  Kvitova, No. 2 in the WTA Tour rankings, was unbeaten in
her four singles matches in the competition, including a victory
over top-ranked  Caroline Wozniacki  of Denmark. Berdych, ranked
seventh on the ATP Tour, also won his four singles matches.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
